---
import ComponentLayout from '../../layouts/ComponentLayout.astro';
---

<ComponentLayout title="Components Showcase">
  <h1>Interactive Components</h1>
  
  <p>This library of framework-agnostic Web Components is designed to bring Prime Period Theory (PPT) to life. These components are highly composable, completely atomic, and independently distributable.</p>

  <p>Explore the component families:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="/components/primitives"><strong>Foundational Primitives</strong></a>: The Base Component, Title, Container, and Text Panels.</li>
    <li><a href="/components/notation"><strong>Notation Components</strong></a>: The Uniform Solfege glyph and the Solfege Phrase Panel.</li>
    <li><a href="/components/geometry"><strong>Geometric Containers</strong></a>: The Period, Period Step, and Sequencer Components.</li>
    <li><a href="/components/controls"><strong>Interactive Controls & Event Bus</strong></a>: Control Panels, Boolean Toggles, and Integer Inputs that communicate via a shared EventBus.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="showcases" style="margin-top: 3rem;">Compositions & Showcases</h2>
  <p>The true power of these atomic components comes from how they can be composed together. Explore these showcases to see the components in action.</p>

  <div class="showcase-grid">
    <a href="/components/showcase/tonal-clock" class="showcase-card">
      <div class="card-thumb" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--prime-3), var(--prime-5));">
        <span style="font-size: 3rem;">⏱️</span>
      </div>
      <div class="card-content">
        <h3>Tonal Clock</h3>
        <p>A circular period arranging 12 semantic pitch elements.</p>
      </div>
    </a>

    <a href="/components/showcase/metronome" class="showcase-card">
      <div class="card-thumb" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--prime-2), var(--prime-7));">
        <span style="font-size: 3rem;">🎛️</span>
      </div>
      <div class="card-content">
        <h3>Metronome</h3>
        <p>A working metronome built with a linear period and sequencer.</p>
      </div>
    </a>

    <a href="/components/showcase/solfege-writer" class="showcase-card">
      <div class="card-thumb" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--solfege-mi), var(--solfege-so));">
        <span style="font-size: 3rem;">✍️</span>
      </div>
      <div class="card-content">
        <h3>Solfege Writer</h3>
        <p>An interactive environment to experiment with Uniform Solfege kerning and layout.</p>
      </div>
    </a>

    <a href="/components/designer" class="showcase-card">
      <div class="card-thumb" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--brand-primary), var(--brand-accent));">
        <span style="font-size: 3rem;">✨</span>
      </div>
      <div class="card-content">
        <h3>Designer Studio</h3>
        <p>A drag-and-drop workspace to visually compose PPT components.</p>
      </div>
    </a>
  </div>

</ComponentLayout>

<style>
  .showcase-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(280px, 1fr));
    gap: 2rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 4rem;
  }
  .showcase-card {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    background: #fff;
    border: 1px solid var(--border-color, #e2e8f0);
    border-radius: 8px;
    overflow: hidden;
    text-decoration: none;
    color: inherit;
    transition: transform 0.2s ease, box-shadow 0.2s ease;
  }
  html.dark .showcase-card {
    background: #1e293b;
    border-color: #334155;
  }
  .showcase-card:hover {
    transform: translateY(-4px);
    box-shadow: 0 10px 15px -3px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1), 0 4px 6px -2px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05);
  }
  .card-thumb {
    height: 160px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color, #e2e8f0);
  }
  html.dark .card-thumb {
    border-bottom-color: #334155;
  }
  .card-content {
    padding: 1.5rem;
  }
  .card-content h3 {
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem 0;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
  }
  .card-content p {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: #64748b;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }
  html.dark .card-content p {
    color: #94a3b8;
  }
</style>
